Sterol regulatory element-binding protein cleavage-activating protein
(SREBP cleavage-activating protein) (SCAP).
"Sterol resistance in CHO cells traced to point mutation in SREBP
cleavage-activating protein.";
"Sterols regulate cycling of SREBP cleavage-activating protein (SCAP)
between endoplasmic reticulum and Golgi.";
"Topology of SREBP cleavage-activating protein, a polytopic membrane
protein with a sterol-sensing domain.";
"Overexpression of membrane domain of SCAP prevents sterols from
inhibiting SCAP.SREBP exit from endoplasmic reticulum.";
-!- FUNCTION: Sterol sensor. Necessary for the proteolytic activation
    of SREBPs by site-1 protease in the Golgi.
-!- SUBUNIT: In a tight complex with SREBs.
-!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Endoplasmic reticulum; endoplasmic reticulum
    membrane; multi-pass membrane protein. Golgi apparatus; Golgi
    apparatus membrane; multi-pass membrane protein. Note=Moves from
    the endoplasmic reticulum to the Golgi in the absence of sterols.
-!- SIMILARITY: Contains 1 SSD (sterol-sensing) domain.
-!- SIMILARITY: Contains 7 WD repeats.
